Read this before you try micro needling at home -
DO’s ✅
•Apply after cleansing and toning
Use Reedle Shot 100 as the first step in your evening skincare routine, after cleansing and toning.

•Use daily for optimal results
For most skin types, daily application is recommended.

•Perform a patch test before full application
Especially if you have sensitive skin, test the product on a small area before using it on your entire face.

•Follow with a moisturizer
After the essence has absorbed, apply a moisturizer to lock in hydration and soothe the skin.

•Store properly
Keep the product in a cool, dry place, away from direct sunlight and heat, to maintain its efficacy.

DON’Ts ❌

•Avoid use on broken or irritated skin
Do not apply Reedle Shot 100 to open wounds, cuts, or areas with active irritation.

•Do not combine with higher strength Reedle Shots
Avoid using it alongside Reedle Shot 300 or 700, as this may cause excessive irritation.

•Refrain from using with certain skincare devices
Do not use Reedle Shot 100 with heat or light-producing devices like LED masks.

•Avoid use immediately after cosmetic procedures
If you’ve had treatments like laser therapy or chemical peels, wait until your skin is fully healed.

•Discontinue use if irritation occurs
If you experience redness, swelling, or discomfort, stop using the product and consult a dermatologist.

Hope it helps 🌷
